          AVB has a tough job moving Chelsea forward and players like Terry, Lampard and Drogba still have too much control and influence over the club in my opinion. Both Cole and Terry could be missing, which might mean an inexperienced Chelsea sit a little deeper, and this wouldnt suit Napolis counter attacking style. However Chelsea have been poor recently against sides that dont have the quality that Napoli do, and will struggle to keep things tight. AVB has struggled in the Premiership, but a couple of their better performances have come in Europe (where he might feel more comfortable). Napoli have lost just twice at home all season, and should have enough tonight, they look a decent bet at 2.3.
